 "name": "Dmitry Kalashnikov"}, {"authorId": "8080821", "name": "Megha Nawhal"}, {"authorId": "2676352", "name": "Sercan Ö. Arik"}, {"authorId": "2363319132", "name": "Hanwen Chen"}, {"authorId": "14564467", "name": "M. Blokzijl"}, {"authorId": "2300566992", "name": "Shubham Gupta"}, {"authorId": "2265401139", "name": "J. Rubin"}, {"authorId": "2037297118", "name": "Rigel Swavely"}, {"authorId": "2273670422", "name": "Sophie Bridgers"}, {"authorId": "8616871", "name": "I. Gemp"}, {"authorId": "2378480006", "name": "Chenlin Su"}, {"authorId": "2304967488", "name": "A. Suggala"}, {"authorId": "2362496726", "name": "Juliette Pluto"}, {"authorId": "147433059", "name": "Mary Cassin"}, {"authorId": "3363862", "name": "Alain C. Vaucher"}, {"authorId": "2374473800", "name": "Kaiyang Ji"}, {"authorId": "2374430619", "name": "J. Cai"}, {"authorId": "31728717", "name": "Andrew Audibert"}, {"authorId": null, "name": "Animesh Sinha"}, {"authorId": "2352238566", "name": "David Tian"}, {"authorId": "2265182544", "name": "E. Farkash"}, {"authorId": "2076366241", "name": "Amy Hua"}, {"authorId": "2249566095", "name": "Jilin Chen"}, {"authorId": "2354146605", "name": "Duc Tran"}, {"authorId": "3213150", "name": "E. Loper"}, {"authorId": "2373037875", "name": "Nicole Brichtova"}, {"authorId": "2065132876", "name": "Lara McConnaughey"}, {"authorId": "2373038091", "name": "Ballie Sandhu"}, {"authorId": "2320955679", "name": "Robert Leland"}, {"authorId": "2245226118", "name": "Douglas DeCarlo"}, {"authorId": "2373034976", "name": "A. Over"}, {"authorId": "2372612723", "name": "J. Huang"}, {"authorId": null, "name": "Xing Wu"}, {"authorId": "2351579038", "name": "C. Fan"}, {"authorId": "2326301768", "name": "Eric Li"}, {"authorId": "2262425515", "name": "Yun-Peng Lei"}, {"authorId": "2374196709", "name": "Deepak Sharma"}, {"authorId": "3316271", "name": "Cosmin Paduraru"}, {"authorId": "2372353361", "name": "Luo Yu"}, {"authorId": "1471340201", "name": "Matko Bovsnjak"}, {"authorId": "2275181671", "name": "Phuong Dao"}, {"authorId": "2349735740", "name": "Min Choi"}, {"authorId": "2131614068", "name": "Sneha Kudugunta"}, {"authorId": "50290651", "name": "Jakub Adamek"}, {"authorId": "2373037657", "name": "Carlos Gu'ia"}, {"authorId": "2316558711", "name": "Ali Khodaei"}, {"authorId": "2350685577", "name": "Jie Feng"}, {"authorId": "2313916188", "name": "Wenjun Zeng"}, {"authorId": "2373036660", "name": "David Welling"}, {"authorId": "2273559338", "name": "Sandeep Tata"}, {"authorId": "2275166845", "name": "Christina Butterfield"}], "abstract": "In this report, we introduce the Gemini 2.X model family: Gemini 2.5 Pro and Gemini 2.5 Flash, as well as our earlier Gemini 2.0 Flash and Flash-Lite models. Gemini 2.5 Pro is our most capable model yet, achieving SoTA performance on frontier coding and reasoning benchmarks. In addition to its incredible coding and reasoning skills, Gemini 2.5 Pro is a thinking model that excels at multimodal understanding and it is now able to process up to 3 hours of video content. Its unique combination of long context, multimodal and reasoning capabilities can be combined to unlock new agentic workflows. Gemini 2.5 Flash provides excellent reasoning abilities at a fraction of the compute and latency requirements and Gemini 2.0 Flash and Flash-Lite provide high performance at low latency and cost. Taken together, the Gemini 2.X model generation spans the full Pareto frontier of model capability vs cost, allowing users to explore the boundaries of what is possible with complex agentic problem solving."}